##When my mother died, I finally met my father and son at the Shelter Hospital

Micro-signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

I mean, we're here to treat patients, and a place like this, built on a shoestring, should do just fine. Times like these, people need to forgive each other. I also believe that everything will be fine once the epidemic is over.

Dictation | Li Tian

Finishing | Ying Chen

I am 43 years old, in Wuhan Qiao Estuary Tax Bureau work. I was a very sunny single mother, ready to get married on February 2 this year. But because of this silent battle, all of a sudden there was nothing.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Li said she had been an optimistic single mother before the outbreak

It was my mother who first developed a cough on the night of January 24. By January 25th, it was getting a little worse, with a low-grade fever of around 38.5.

My father works in Nanjing. He came home years ago. On January 20th, I stopped working because I called in early. From that day on, the whole family was at home and had not been to any gathering place. My father is Chinese medicine, chief physician, my mother is Western medicine, my own junior college is also learning Chinese medicine. So we all thought mother just a common cold and fever, at home to give her own infusion. Her fever did go down.

But over the next few days, four of my family members began to feel sick, but none had a fever. Like, my whole body hurts, my neck hurts, and I thought it was a cervical thing. Seriously, four of us, three of US medical students, had no idea it was gonna get infected. We were all very careful.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Family photo

On January 30th, my mother suddenly became unwell and said she was feeling ill. And I saw that it wasn't good. I ran to the open door in the neighborhood and asked the security guard if I could open the one near my house. Because now every block is closed, the only open door, I am holding the mother to walk to the words to more than 10 minutes. But they said no, so there's nothing to be done. I went back to the community and told them what was going on at my house, and asked if they had sent a car to take my mother to a designated hospital, but they told me to take her to a designated forward health facility.

That day, my own body is still pain, but the family only me, fortunately at that time still can drive, sent my mother there. The other side can only do chest X-ray, recommended that I go to a major hospital for further CT. The closest hospital to our house was Concord Hospital, but I knew it would be overcrowded, and there was no way my mom would be standing in line. I drove my mom to a remote hospital in Jiang'an District, and when the C.T. was done, the doctor said it could be neopneumonia. But they don't have it here.

My mom grabbed me and said she couldn't breathe. I rushed her off to Concord. At the fever clinic, I just got down on my knees and said, somebody help my mom. She's dying. Fortunately, a person like the head nurse, immediately find a wheelchair to the mother to oxygen, this was relieved. I gave my mom all the tests I could do that day, including the nucleic acid test. I did a nucleic acid test of my own.

It's horrible in the I.V. room. It's full of oxygen people. My mother had been sitting outside the IV room that day, but it was very cold. I went to the doctor to see if I could arrange a hospital stay. Doctors say all the new crown cases go to concord West, but there are no more beds there. I know all about it. I don't expect a bed. I just kept asking for a doctor's appointment, even if it was for observation. Finally, the doctor asked me to take my mother to the fourth floor observation room. It's a room for two, and I really appreciate it, and I'm satisfied.

But my mom was already in bad shape, had a bed, couldn't lie down, breathed, and was confined to a wheelchair. It was during this time that I learned that my mother had accompanied my uncle to the hospital once, and that my uncle had been admitted to Wuhan Central Hospital as a newly diagnosed patient.

In this case, after settling my mother, I immediately rented a bed-and-breakfast across from the hospital, went home to clean up a bit, took my son and father to live, a room isolation. At the time, my son also had a slight fever, and my father was very weak.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A photo of Li Tian on Wechat

On January 31, my son had a fever of 103. I rushed him to the hospital. My Dad wouldn't go, said he couldn't walk. The son had a needle hanging in the hospital and a nucleic acid test. The next day, I dragged my father to the hospital to do the nucleic acid.

Finally, the test results came out, my mother is double strong Yang confirmed, my father and I are Shuangyang District confirmed, my son Shan Yang confirmed. The test results were mixed, and I never got a text from my mom, which was supposed to be for confirmed patients. At first, the doctor assured me that if I didn't get it, I wouldn't. I insisted that the doctor use the computer to check for me, and sure enough, it was a definite diagnosis.

I myself was a confirmed patient, for a few days, dragging such a body, can be said to be three parts to take care of family members. Luckily, in the last act of mercy, I had no symptoms, or this family would have collapsed. It's a good thing I didn't give it to my fiance, but he couldn't do anything to help me. He also has a paralyzed mother in his family to care for.

When I got the confirmation report, I called the community again, asked them what to do, and all they said was that they would report it. On the afternoon of February 3rd, I received a call from the community asking us to wait at the Red Cross hospital. It was said that patients with mild cases like ours would be arranged to go to the shelter hospital. So I drove them there, and I went back to Concorde to take care of my mother. That night, my dad was in an empty bed, and my son was sitting on the bench all night.

At the time, I didn't know what was going on at the shelter hospital, but it gave me a break. At least my son and dad didn't have to worry so much. I could focus on my mom. She's really not well. She can't eat, she can't drink, she's on fluids. There's no cure for the disease now, only immunity. I've spent twenty thousand bucks on Protein infusions for her.

On Feb. 4, the son and father were taken to a designated hotel to wait. But that day, my mother's condition took a turn for the worse. Her face was swollen and her oxygen level had gone from 90 to sixty. The doctor how to do not get better, watching my mother with tubes all over, I struggled for a long time, and the doctor finally said, "forget it, do not want to see my mother pain. ". They had to carry my mother to bed by four people, and she was already incontinent and her wheelchair was all wet.

I made a video call to my son so he could see his grandmother one last time. My son and my mother are very close, when he shouted: "Grandma you cheer up, you have to get better. " And my father refused to face. My Son told me that my grandfather had been lying in bed, refusing to speak or speak to him. I know. My Dad was devastated.

In the early morning hours of February 5th, my mother finally didn't make it, and her whole body was swollen. I watched her swallow her last breath, the pupil slowly dilated, tears have not know how much left. My mother blamed me for not seeing me these days. I really can not, except a few head to run, every time the doctor prescribed what medicine, because it is full reimbursement, have to go to the registration and then go to the designated place to get, far away.

Patients like this have to be taken care of, so the hospital called me, told me to contact the funeral home myself. Then they came quickly, took her away in yellow and white bags, and told me to pick up the ashes in 15 days.

Deal with the mother's funeral, too late to grieve for too long, I also went to the Red Cross hospital and so on, but because the first batch of time I was not. On the night of February 5, my son and my father were first taken to the Kong Hon Shelter Hospital at the Wuhan International Convention and Exhibition Center. They were among the first to be photographed by Xinhua.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The son and father were on their way to the hospital

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The child in the picture is Li Tian's 15-year-old son, with her 71-year-old father wearing a blue cap (photo: Xinhua) 

I spent the night in a hospital chair, and I heard we were scheduled.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
She spent the night alone in a Red Cross hospital chair

February 6, and my son Wechat communication that he and my father is next to the two beds, where they were issued with toiletries. It's got power, it's got electric blankets. It's not that the power is out and it's cold online, and it's just awful to post something negative in this situation. But my son says the toilet is really dirty. He said, "mom, you can't stand this kind of toilet. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
He was in a room with 50 people, but with only four doctors and two nurses, it was a little overwhelming.

On the 6th, breakfast was served at about 10:00 in the morning. Simple. And then the evening issued medicine, my son also photographed me to see, are some proprietary Chinese medicine, I feel useless. I made sure that my son would eat well, take care of GRANDPA, and let him eat too, so that he would have the strength to fight the disease.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
And I myself had to wait in the Red Cross hospital, the scene is also very chaotic. On the one hand, the community keeps sending people in, some of whom haven't even been diagnosed yet, but they don't know they're in there; on the other hand, there's no intention of a car taking us. I saw more and more people in the hall, and we were losing patience.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
We were all just sitting there, waiting

I also saw some people were sent back from the shelter, because there are only mild cases, these people's blood oxygen is low, should be sent to the Vulcan Mountain, Thor Mountain, such places. In this way, I sat in the Red Cross Hospital Chair all night, fortunately the hospital is to provide boxed lunch.

On the afternoon of February 7th, many people, like me, had been here for two nights, exhausted by the delay in seeing the arrangements. Someone started to make a scene. The police are here. I, too, am eager to see my father and son.

Finally, a car was arranged to take us all to the shelter hospital. When we arrived, a doctor came to inquire about us, and dinner was served, both well-prepared and hot. But I got there late, so we didn't get our meds. My son said that some traditional Chinese medicine was given out today which claimed to be very effective in treating this disease.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Here is can walk, men and women ward can occasionally visit. But because of my special situation, I told them that my son and father live here, and they let me come and take care of them whenever I want. It's a relief to finally meet them. They're both in good spirits. But I think my dad had a stomach upset from the Chinese medicine.

Li Tian shot the video, think the Shelter Hospital Environment is OK

I think the overall condition is OK, that is, in addition to living in a clean place, the toilet, wash gargle place is really too dirty. However, this morning (February 8) , after a lot of patients protest, the staff has cleaned the toilet, is still quite clean.

Porta-potty

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The water room is still a bit dirty

I get up in the morning some dizziness, the stomach also does not know because took the medicine the relation reaction to be some big, after a while prepares to ask the doctor again. But last night, the doctor told me during rounds that my condition is improving and I believe I can be discharged soon. My father and son are in good condition today, the father also asked to eat preserved eggs lean meat congee, I gave him a take-away.

Around 13:00 today, the hospital served lunch and handed out fruit

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Family photo at the Shelter Hospital

I mean, we're here to treat patients, and this is a makeshift place where basic living conditions can be met. Times like these, people need to forgive each other. These days, I've called the mayor's hotline, and I've reached out to the community, and despite the difficulties, they've all helped me a lot in the end, including my unit. In the meantime, we all for a variety of reasons, there are emotions inevitable, but now look back on it, must still believe in the government. I'm sure things will get better soon.
